<br>
If you have a track record of running small multi group hits and express an interest in running big shows - you can make the big hit raid leader list.<br>
<br>
From Jahras - he put 4 peeps on the list - Serano, Pensfan, Arielyn, and Solairs.<br>
<br>
Any thursday that is not taken before you post a hit - can be a training ground for a player that is working to hone their raid leading skills - and running events.  You are also encouraged to run multi group affairs to finish quests or exploration expiditions on Wednesdays, sat and Sundays that are not being used by some event<br>
<br>
I have been watching Arkard, Del, Azzenkar, Hedorm and uhhh I might be missing someone - throw together a couple multi group events.  Please go ahead and send me a tell if you are considering running something big and are not sure if it is a good thing for you to run.  Let me know if you want to do a small multi group hit and you have any questions.<br>
<br>
Don't let my overbearing command presence, strip you of the chance to run an event and get experiance running something.  There are a couple places where I just know every inch of the zone and I am so used to running the pace I will take over if you are slack.  Let me know if I step on your toes so you can run your event.  My goal is to NOT be all in charge and all when it is your event - but don't wig out when I give you tempo advice.<br>
<br>
<br>
THE BOTTOM LINE - if you schedule a BIG hit and I or pensfan are not confidant in the success of the operation - we might either lock/ cancel it - or take it over or postpone it pending a tell session.  This isn't to hinder your ability to grow but to better focus guild resources to successes vs time sinks.<br>
<br>
The end goal I have in mind is that I can back seat most raids instead of running them all.  I will obviously be likely to be running raids until TF burns up when the Earth falls into the sun. But contrary to the notion that a guild MUST have one raid leader (or two) I think everyone should aspire to ultimatly replace their leaders.<br>
<br>
You guys know that I am in the military and I am currently in command of an Army Company (its only a BN HQ Compnay- meh).  In the army there are 2 types of leaders (ok dozens but that is besides the point) there is a guy that is in love with power and strives to get it - won't let go as he gains any and seeks more.  And there is a guy that wants things done right.  In the process of making things right he mentors all of his Jr Leaders to ultimatly, take over all of his power and jobs so that when they are ready to take over the transition is painless for them.<br>
<br>
My goal is that if I hand a raid to Azzenkar to run, everyone is happy because he will run it better than I would.  Azzenkar just being a name out of the hat  - no particular preferance to anyone living nor dead is intended.<br>
<br>
Have a nice day.<br>
<br>
Serano<br>
